---js
{
	title: 'Zibaldone',
	permalink: '/zibenglish/',
	redirect_from: ['/blog/', '/en/zibaldone/'],
	ref: 'Zibaldone',
	description: 'Things getting out of Tommi’s head, in the form of articles',
	type: 'CollectionPage',
	sitemap: {
		priority: 0.8,
		changefreq: 'monthly',
	},
	eleventyImport: {
		collections: ['zibaldone'],
	},
	updated: function (data) {
		return this.collections.zibaldone[0].data.date
	}
}
---
<main class='list'>
	<hgroup class='flex'>
		<h1 class='wavyBackgroundPurple'>Zibaldone</h1>
	</hgroup>

	<article class='e-content'>
		<p><em>Zibaldone di Pensieri</em> is a great collection of notes by the great Italian author <a href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Giacomo_Leopardi' title='Giacomo Leopardi on Wikipedia'>Giacomo Leopardi</a>. This blog has its same name because it shares the same vibes, but less than a fraction of the literary value of the original.</p>
		<p>Here is my translation of the literal definition of the word, from the <a href='https://treccani.it' target='_blank' hreflang='it' title='Enciclopedia Treccani'>Treccani encyclopedia</a>:</p>
		<blockquote><p><a href='https://treccani.it/vocabolario/zibaldone/' hreflang='it' lang='it' target='_blank'>Żibaldóne</a>, […] notebook where unordered news, notes, thoughts, quotes, schemes, sketches are noted. Exactly that.</p></blockquote>
	</article>

	<aside class='subgrid'>
		<div class='two-thirds'>
			{% render 'tags.liquid', site: site %}
		</div>
		<div class='one-third'>
			{% render 'lang-filter.liquid', lang: lang %}
		</div>
	</aside>

	<div class='entries-list subgrid'>
		<input type='checkbox' id='langFilter-en' class='langFilter'>
		<input type='checkbox' id='langFilter-it' class='langFilter'>
		<input type='checkbox' id='langFilter-fr' class='langFilter'>
		<input type='checkbox' id='langFilter-all' class='langFilter'>
		{% for entry in collections.zibaldone %}
			<a class='one-third background box' href='{{ entry.url }}' hreflang='{{ entry.data.lang }}'>
				<h2>{{ entry.data.title }}</h2>
				<figure>
					{% if entry.data.image %}<img src='{{ entry.data.image }}' alt='{{ entry.data.title }}'>{% endif %}
				</figure>
				<p class='center'>{% if entry.data.location %}{{ entry.data.location }}, {% endif %}<time class='dt-published' datetime='{{ entry.date | date_to_xmlschema }}'>{{ entry.date | date: '%-d %B %Y' }}</time></p>
				{% render 'entry-tags.liquid', tags: entry.data.tags, site: site, size: 'tiny' %}
			</a>
		{% endfor %}
	</div>
</main>
